Texture comment: Fresh plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomero-porphyritic dacitic rock (pebbles) or lava. Fine-grained volcanic origin xenolith (up tp 2 mm) in the groundmass. Moderately vesiculated. Vesicles are elongated and oriented. Seawater-origin halite precipitated in the tiny cracks.
Groundmass comments: Quenched glass lines on the outer surface and surface of vesicle, and small-sized (up to 2 mm) xenolith.
Phenocryst 1 comments: some present in clots of plagioclase with pyroxene.
Vesicle comments: 20% of very elongated and oriented sub-rounded vesicles.
